license: MIT
abstract: >
  ConfusionMapper is a Python desktop application for inter-rater reliability
  (IRR) computation in cognitive error taxonomy research. It operationalises a
  two-rater classification workflow — human researcher and AI rater — over
  multiple-choice question distractors, computes Cohen's kappa, and visualises
  agreement through an interactive dashboard.
keywords:
  - inter-rater reliability
  - Cohen's kappa
  - cognitive error classification
  - educational research
  - adaptive learning
  - educational data mining
  - Python
